text: Hatımillet (, ) or Ihtimillet (), Ihtaimlat (), also spelled Ihtaymilat, Ahtaymalat or Hetemlat, is a town in northern Aleppo Governorate, northwestern Syria. Located some north of the city of Aleppo, it administratively belongs to Nahiya Sawran in Azaz District. Nearby localities include Sawran to the west and Dabiq to the south. In the 2004 census, Ihtaimlat had a population of 6,764. ==References== Category:Turkmen communities in Syria Category:Syrian people of Turkish descent Category:Turkish-speaking territories in Syria
